b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Hypotenuse AI is best suited for product descriptions, batch content, ecommerce, SEO articles, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. ShortlyAI, meanwhile, shines for blog posts, long form articles, stories, distraction free writing, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2020, Hypotenuse AI describes itself as \"AI writing platform for ecommerce and batch content creation.\" ShortlyAI, established in 2020, positions itself as \"Distraction-free AI writing tool focused on long-form content.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Hypotenuse AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 5.0), more features (9 vs 2), more competitive pricing, availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean ShortlyAI is a poor choice — far from it. ShortlyAI excels in its own right, particularly for blog posts and long form articles.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent batch generation for product catalogs, go with Hypotenuse AI. If clean distraction-free interface matters more to you, ShortlyAI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
